Vice President Biden is scheduled to travel to Detroit, Michigan on August 5th to deliver remarks on the economy. He will discuss the steps taken to rescue the economy and the long-term investments being made to rebuild for the future. The event is open to the public, with a limited number of tickets available on a first-come, first-served basis. The press is invited to cover the event and must RSVP by August 4th. The event will take place at NextEnergy in Detroit.